description: Jean-Michel Ponzio was born in 1967 in Rognac. After studying communication, he made short films in 3D and sets for advertising and film (Batman & Robin, Fight Club, Heaven). In 2001, he signed his first illustrations for publications I read, before turning to the comics. In 2004, he released his first album published by Sun, written by Laurent Genefort news. He then published the comic adaptation of the sci-fi novel, The Eye of Purgatory, published by Carabas. Later, his collaboration with Richard Marazano reinforces his reputation as an ultra-realistic designer. He continues to design parallel universes for advertising and movies alike. French Language.
name: Vol. 1

description: Iris is the perfect marriage of artificial intelligence and virtual reality, serving as the backbone for enhanced reality contact lenses that provide users with the perfect antidote to reality's many maladies. From pop-culture inspired fantasies to manifestations of their personal imagining, they see the world precisely as they wish. To ensure societal tranquility, citizens of cView City are fitted with a pair of lenses at birth, but when Aldair--a teenage programming heiress--gets a glimpse of life with her own eyes, the world she once knew irrevocably changes forever.

Spirou and Fantasio, in transit through Paris airport, are kidnapped by French counter-intelligence: in exchange for the release of two French nationals from Soviet prisons, the KGB demanded the two reporters’ assistance. Because Moscow has a problem: the mob is getting increasingly powerful and bold, and it has infiltrated the authorities so thoroughly they can’t fight back anymore. They do know, however, that the big boss is someone Spirou and Fantasio have met before and simply cannot ignore…
name: In Moscow

description: Colette, Violet, Pamela, Nicky, and Paulina are working on a historical restoration when they learn about an ancient Viking vessel that sank off the shore of Whale Island. Rumor has it that the ship is full of treasure, and what's worse, some shadowy figure is plotting to steal it! If Mouseford's best investigative journalists can't crack this case, Whale Island will lose one of its most important cultural artifacts before it's even found.
name: The Treasure of the Viking Ship

description: CHRISTOPHER MITTEN RETURNS to draw the concluding story arc of this truly epic saga! Michael, Abi, and Thomas have found The Golden Sea, just as the Oracle predicted. But will it lead them to A-Ree-Yass-I? And if it does, what will they find? Questions will be answered, secrets revealed... and not everyone will get out alive!
name: The Final Chapter Part One: Breath of Ghosts

description: Translates : All-New X-Men (2013) #17 , X-Men Legacy (2013) #14-15 , X-Men (2013) #06
name: La Battaglia dell'atomo : capitolo 5

description: Translates : Uncanny X-Men (2013) #13 , Cable and X-Force (2013) #13-14 , X-Men: Gold #01
name: La Battaglia dell'atomo : capitolo 6

description: When her niece, missing for almost a year, shows up on her doorstep with a horrifying secret, Carol Hogarth will find out that people can be poison...especially if that person is named Virginia Applejack. Find out what best friends, worst enemies, an artificial leg, and a bottle of rum all have to do with "THE KILLER WHO AWOKE BEFORE DAWN."
name: Sweet Jane

description: Re-presenting the first two sold-out issues of Steve Niles and Bernie Wrightson’s monster masterwork, in one handy volume! See what all the critical acclaim is for, in time for the third issue, because the first two are long gone…

description: The Green Lantern ring for space sector 2813 was inactive for years after Krypton’s end, until the creation of the Argo colony recalled it to service. As none of Zod’s followers are suitable candidates, the ring’s search brings it to the nearest Kryptonian it can recruit! SMALLVILLE SEASON 11 continues in “Lantern” part 1 of 4!
name: Lantern, Part 1

volume.name: No Need for Tenchi! Part Twelve

description: This year's sketchbook is a digest-sized special limited to 1000 signed copies.
A concurrent second sketchbook for 2007, also digest sized, this one featuring Linsner and non-Linsner characters that are NOT Dawn.

The Actress

A popular actress finds herself abducted from her house and institutionalized in the 51 Serif St. house. As she is thrown in a cell she begins the journey to discovering who sent her there and why, and soon realizes that she may not be alone. But her cell-mate may not be something she is prepared to face.
name: The Actress

description: Archer Coe meets Hope Midland and begins her treatment, using his hypnosis to dive into her mind and ferret out the truth behind her marital problems with Jack. But what Archer sees doesn't match what Jack's been telling him, and Hope seems to be hiding secrets even he can't uncover.
name: Chapter 3: Mrs. Lonely

volume.name: Archer Coe and the Thousand Natural Shocks

description:
Keeper of Secrets!

Will Steve keep the secret behind the AWF?

Who is Rita?

Why is she asking for Yvette's help?

The answers to these questions are found in this issue.

Betty and Veronica jet off to fabulous New York City for a runway event hosted by an old friend of Mrs. Lodge's. It promises to be the hottest fashion affair of the season... until a mysterious ailment befalls all of the models and threatens to doom the entire production! Betty and Veronica may end up as more than just purveyors of the show if it's to go on! Featuring special guest appearances from Sabrina the Teenage Witch, Josie and the Pussycats, Katy Keene, Ginger Snapp, and more classic characters!

Note: The digital edition (4/16/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Fashion Fantabulous!

description:
The Arrival of the Chrononauts

For our next experiment, take a quantum leap back to the origins of the calamitous community of Haven Hallows as one resident is sent hurtling through time to bear witness to the ... Arrival of THE CHRONONAUTS!
name: The Arrival of the Chrononauts

description:
Can Bo fight back from his coma?? Perhaps, if he can take out the next big boss in the "Roswell" gang, Serpent (a.k.a. Puppet Master)!!

It's plushy teddy vs. alien mutant gang warfare... can you dig it?!?!
name: Part 3

description:
Origin of the Species Part 2

Issue 2 ramps up the intensity as the Vidulars start seeking which Earthlings can wield the powers of the eight holy items. We also see how the battle between Epica and The Harmony over the skies of Singapore is going, as well as meet two new characters who join the fray.
name: Origin of the Species Part 2

description:
After the massive battle with Bomb Queen, Mercury has once again teleported the Muse and Badger to another world. In this 3rd installment, the trio find themselves encased in a Mayan pyramid, where they cross paths with Marat Mychaels' "Demon Slayer." Jaclyn, the newly appointed slayer, is still being trained by the monk Tenzin. In this massive tomb, they track the trickster demon called Golic, who wants to escape to the mortal world. Everything was going to plan, until Mercury, Muse and Badger fall out of a teleportation disc. Now Golic has possessed the Demon Slayer to fight Muse and her allies. It's a battle royal as the power of the Greek gods collides with the mystical Demon Slayer. Featuring Mike Baron's "The Badger."

name: Round Three

description: Check out a behind the scenes of this manga series! Three friends from the streets of New York reunite when one of their friends is mysteriously murdered by an ex-superhero. Jonathan Diesel, millionaire and bounty hunter, is contracted by the government to track down the killer. As events unfold, Diesel discovers the killer is not only his former hero, but also his uncle.
Devah versus Decoda! Will Lilyth's plan to control both twins succeed or is she asking for double trouble? Plus, a surprising revelation about Joseph Caine is revealed!

Tales Of Wrath

Back after much critical acclaim! It's Freestyle! The comic no-one thought would make it past the first issue! Created by Australian Mark Pursell who likes to think he can draw and write and stuff and occasionally can, Freestyle is a comic. It is funny and has words and pretty pictures!

In this issue! It's the start of a whole new trilogy! Chloe unleashes another of her crappy schemes! This time she is raising early designs of Stupid Cat from the grave and making them try and kill the current version of Stupid Cat, starting with Stupid Cat from 1995... What is the reason behind her scheme? It's bound to be something stupid and annoying but she must be stopped at all costs!
name: Tales Of Wrath

description: When an info source gives Gina a lead on a rare access to a "millennium crypt", she's only got time to collect her sister Britanny and new student Ayane Anno for aid before the chance passes. Her research says they've cracked open the equivalent of an abandoned storage locker, but what they find is one of the enigmatic Death Trap Architech's strongholds!

People are struggling with their loss of identity after The Healing. Dr. Daniel Rivers, a leading cancer researcher, struggles after his life's work - and career - seem to have disappeared overnight. The members of a small support group are left to wonder if their illnesses are real or just in their heads. And Donna Gibbs continues her search for the cause of The Healing by investigating a most curious death - A natural one.

Seeking Samarkand Part 4 of 8

Haunted forest? Check.

Soul-sucking Demon? Check.

Pirates and Taverns? Check.

Romance? Half a check.

As the Lost Kids do their best to live another day, old friendships will be put to the test, new alliances will be forged and adventure continues as new clues about Samarkand surface. Oh, and did we mention the Soul-sucking Demon?

Allegiances

As the noose tightens around him, John Morris finally finds his way back home into the arms of his wife. But is he the man she wants to see? With the police, the mob, and Perpes Caliga closing in on him, John has the answers he has been searching for, but will those answers shake his faith further?

description:
On the eve of the MEGA MAN/MEGA MAN X Crossover comes the TWISTED tale that could only be called "A Chance at Redemption!" Dr. Wily is a free man, cleared of wrongdoing, and it's all thanks to -- Mega Man?! Can even an evil villain like himself live with a lie of that magnitude? Can he enjoy a life of robotics research next to his "frenemy" Dr. Light? Will the promise of power in Gamma be far too tempting? The answer to all your burning questions lie in this mega-fun issue! Includes cover art by Patrick "SPAZ" Spaziante!

description: Immortal Victor has been captured by a cult that worships his ancient enemy, the demon Azazuul. Deprived of his magic weapons, Victor must rely on those he has sworn to protect in order to survive.

The stunning and tragic conclusion to this story about a man who returns from the dead. Fans of gothic romance stories will enjoy this epic love story about death.

The curse of the mummy has never been stronger in this relationship. Fans of Hammer Films and other classic horror stories should check this out.

volume.name: Necrotic: Dead Flesh On A Living Body

description: A nurse longs for the past, can't wait for the future, and struggles to figure out the present.

Midnight Dreary

Nightwatcher Captain Corvan Moore is coerced into clearing a shipment of dreamdust into Cog Town if he wants to see his daughter again. What does the ship's first mate, a celestial, know about Corvan, and how is he connected to Sheriff Gearwall? Corvan's bloodline holds answers, but is he ready to accept them?

Cover is an homage to Da Vinci's Vitruvian Man.
name: Midnight Dreary

description: The mystery deepens backstage while Rob and Heidi become full-fledged members of The Ten.

From the pages of Bust magazine and Unlovable Book 1, the sometimes ordinary, sometimes humiliating, often poignant and frequently hilarious exploits of '80s teen underdog Tammy Pierce: big hair, boogers, boys and other high school pitfalls. Learn how to kiss using household objects, shoplifting do's and don'ts PLUS the effects of raspberry wine coolers.
name: Ghouls Just Wanna Have Fun!

description: Rue discovers evidence of Quinn, Jade fights a giant, and the compnions discover a secret map room left by Quinn.
name: The Bridge of No Return

description:
Archie and Dilton are embarking on a new business venture: aerial photography! The boys are ready to make history, but what happens when their new invention lands in a no-fly zone? Find out in 'In Plane View,' the lead story to an entertaining double digest!

Note: The digital edition (4/16/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: In 'Plane' View

description: Digested #03 further unfolds the 'Oxygen' storyline and introduces us to the world of 'Minimum Hours' along with more of Bobby.N's "shorts'.
